caption: We got the chaat, chicken curry, chana masala, chicken momos, carrot halwa and mango cheesecake for dessert. Everything was delicious, my favorites were the momos, chaat, and the dessert. Definitely would go back again.

I've been meaning to try Vajra for years and I'm so glad I finally did! Everything I ordered was amazing and flavorful. The date night package was plenty for two people and we still had leftovers. This will become a go-to spot!
Excellent customer service great wine an awesome coffee
High quality, extremely tasty and authentic South Asian food. They understand which dishes should be appropriately spicy.

Havent dined in yet . Have always packed food to go ! The food has been flavorful every time.  Ordered their Thanksgiving menu. It was nothing short of spectacular! Right from the ordering process, service to food packing and the taste of each dish! Well done team Vajra!

Picked up a "Dinner Date from Home" meal – my wife and I were blown away.  The cocktail we got (That Villain Name Alphonso) was the perfect sweet, spicy beverage to complement the delicious smoky and earthy Goan Shrimp Curry and Kadhai Lamb.  All the dishes were perfect, and plenty of food for two with more for leftovers!

The meal we ordered from Vajra was the best we have had in months! Every dish was delicious and different, the portions were generous, and the prices were reasonable. I can't wait to be able to go and eat there in person.
Great service and amazing food!

I’ve been hunting for a good Indian place in the city and this did not disappoint. Carry out/delivery ONLY and the wait gets a little long, but let me tell you that it’s worth every minute. I got the aloo mutter and baingan bharta (two of my favorite dishes) and they were a perfect blend of spice and flavor. I will go back.
They simply ignored my delivery order. I typically know how to order on the phone then wait.
We did takeout few days ago. Everything was delicious. Dinner for two can feed 3-4 people easy.
Incredible food! Enjoyed take out over the weekend and it exceeded expectations. High quality ingredients combined into fantastic dishes.
Great food and amazing service!
An abundance of flavorful food. Can taste the quality of their ingredients and the take away packaging (dinner date for two) felt thoughtful made for an amazing meal.
Got takeout today and everything was delicious!! The portions are actually really big so the cost is worth it. Very full and a bunch of leftovers to enjoy tomorrow!

Reading the reviews I had some high expectations from this place.  I ordered the chicken biryani and the dahi bhalla.  Don't get me wrong, the flavors were good, but for a $20 biryani, I would expect some high quality white meat chicken.  Instead it was dark thigh meat and my order actually had some fat cooked in as well.  On to the dahi bhalla, very bland bhalla and one of them was still frozen (enough that I couldn't even break it with a spoon)  while the other two were thawed enough.  Again for the price and quality being advertised, this should not be acceptable.  The yogurt was on the sweet side and it had pomegranate seeds in it too. Overall, I wouldn't say I'm super impressed by this place.  The price they charge doesn't match the quality of food they provide.
Great food - fresh, high quality. Friendly staff and quick delivery.

Did the family meal tonight from Vajra.  It was excellent - well packaged, fresh, piping hot, and the food quality was top notch.   We ordered the saag paneer, cashew tikka masala with chicken, matter paneer, and bhindi masala (my wife is nuts about okra).  The portions were huge - this is easily enough for 2 meals for a family of 4.  We are just a family of 2....so we'll be gladly eating this for days.  Can't wait to come back once the restaurant is open but until then, this family meal is a stellar way to enjoy Indian food at home.  Will certainly be ordering this again before the lock down is over.
(Translated by Google) Crazy briyani  (Original) Crazy briyani
Trust me when I say THIS IS THE BEST INDIAN FOOD in Chicago! Jose makes the best crafted cocktails. Ambience and people are welcoming. This is our go to Indian place for dine in and take out.
Just got some take out absolutely amazing!
Over expensive place. Blah when it comes to spicy food. Americanized Indian food. Not authentic.
The cocktails are awesome. Food too

My friends and I went here for brunch this past Sunday. One of my friends is Nepali so we wanted to see if we were getting an authentic experience. While not on the menu, we special requested MoMo since I had never tried them. The kitchen put them in for us and in about 15 they were out. So delicious and my Nepali friend said the sauce was spot on. We also shared the goat skewers, chicken dum biryani, and some garlic naan with tea. While the bulk of the menu focused moreso on Indian cuisine at least for brunch, the service and ambiance was great 👍🏼
One of my favorite restaurants in the city. The food is always great and has the perfect level of spice. The cocktails are perfect, seasonal, and delicious.

Went here with a friend who is kind of snobby about Indian food and we were both BLOWN AWAY. Every single thing we ordered was so incredibly unique and flavorful and so well priced.  I highly recommend the Tandoori Paneer and the Samosa Chaat, and the gruyere naan was the best thing I’ve eaten in a long time. The Pistachio Paan Kulfi was amazing too! Highly recommend this place and will definitely be returning!!!
This is the best Indian food I've eaten in America and Canada, and that's about 75 different Indian Restaurants. The only thing better was the homemade Indian food from my close friends.

Thank you Vajra for such a great meal! One of the best Indian restaurants I've been to in a very long time.  Not only did they have an amazing cocktail menu wow me (Their head of Beverage is a Chicago recognized cocktail celebrity), but their food was flavorful, fresh, and cooked perfectly.  The lamb wasn't over cooked, the chicken cut with a fork, and their veggies dishes were delicious. I can't recommend this restaurant enough.  I'll definitely be back for their food and drinks!
The meals and service were ahead of my expectations. I truly loved the vibes of this restaurant. Great restaurant to take the family out for lunch.

Quite simply the best Indian restaurant in Chicago. Everything we ate was super tasty, we’ll spiced, and included high quality ingredients! I’m an British Asian from the UK and have an extremely high standard when it comes to Indian food and can say with certainty that Vajra is the only Chicago Indian restaurant that comes close to anything in the UK or indeed India. The Daal Makhani in particular is exquisite. Keep it up Vajra, and hang on to your chef!

I was looking for more ...I loved the chilli paneer ...the spices were right but the paneer was a little rubbery . Everything else was ok we tried dal makhni ...tandoori paneer ..samosa Chaat and aaloo bodi ...I was looking for more in  terms of flavors .. presentation and new experience but everything was regular ...nothing wowed me

Hands down Vajra is the BEST place for Indian cuisine. The drinks are very well made and o was told that the mixologist won an award for the top mixologist in the area. I love the babblers nest - that is something you should definitely try!
Superrrrr Awesome for spicy Indian food. Loved it. Worth little extra bucks you need to spend. Must must visit.

Great place for higher end Indian food - perfect for a date night or evening with friends. We really enjoyed all the curries we tried - especially the cashew tikka and matar paneer. The dahl was also a really delicious side dish. The value was also great and we'll get another meal out of leftovers. My husband enjoyed his gin cocktail, which was nicely balanced. The service was great and everyone was really friendly and attentive. We'll definitely be back!
My new favorite Indian restaurant in chicago. Lots of options for all diet types and food is very tasty!

Located in the space that once occupied one of our favorite restaurants, West Town Tavern, Vajra is more than a suitable successor; it surpasses West Town in many ways. We went for my wife's birthday and we were blown away on the quality, the service and, most importantly, the food. Simply delicious.

Catering Review: hosted friends for Thanksgiving and everyone just loved the food. Goat biryani was packed with flavor, chicken biryani was properly spiced and the chilli chicken appetizer was an instant hit. For the vegetarians in our group bhindi masala was just divine. The owner was ver generous to give us complimentary veg pakoras that were fresh. I would order again in a heartbeat... If you're hosting I hope you try these and be wowed!!!
Exilant in all service but manager Margret could not handle situation she is neglecting future customer she was 5 years old could not provided her chair to seat

First time here and we were blown away. Amazing, unique and interesting cocktails and a great mocktail selection (as a non-drinker).  The service was excellent - we sat at the bar and got served right away.  JuanJo is the best mixologist (vote for him for the Banchet Awards).  We’ll definitely be coming back soon!
This place has a nice ambiance. The food and service was great!
This place is very good, generous portions, very good service. Tasty drinks, pricey.
Can't wait to come back; they delivered great service, food was flavorful but what we really want to try are more of their artful drinks!
Yummy authentic food.

Interesting menu with a focus on Nepalese dishes. Since it was the two of us we weren't able to sample that many dishes. Goat Sikh Kabab was flavorful although a real char was missing on the meat which is hard to do on typical restaurant grill as opposed to a charcoal unit. Baby corn and pea curry was flavorful but more watery than I expected. English peas were mentioned on the menu but  they tasted more like frozen peas - not canned. The Tandoori Chicken was advertised as being flavored with several ingredients but the result was not intense by any means and there were grill marks on the breast which I didn't expect from a Tandoor. Will have to try again.
Super Tasty Chicken Tikka Masala!
Great food, generous portions, and they are very accommodating for dietary restrictions, including vegan. Highly recommend this place!
Amazing experience!! The ambiance is really cool and food is excellent!! Service was stellar as well.
Such a great and delicious place
Nice ambience, good service, and the food is of high quality. Parking depends on the time of the day. A really nice addition to West Town.
Poor service. Inspite of a reservation we were made to wait for 45 mins . Food was still okay.
Large portions, great taste, and amazing atmosphere. I'll definitely be back again soon. Only complaint was that the service was fairly slow and the dining area is very crowded and noisy.

It was my first time trying Indian food and I'm glad I came here for it. The food was all delicious and not too spicy. Had the butter chicken and a couple curry dishes, garlic naan, and the lassi drink. Don't recommend ordering wine, they served very little.

The best Indian restaurant in Chicago. The food is delicious and beautifully presented, the cocktails are incredible, the atmosphere is fun and the service is even better. Also, the gruyere naan is to die for. I have been a few times and cannot wait to go back!
Great authentic Indian food with great service!

Visited Vajra for friends birthday party. Very nice and cozy ambiance.  First glance of the menu it sid not look appealing however after ordering few items they were amazing. We ordered tandoori paneer platter - amazing. Wish it came out in a sizzling platter. We also ordered corn and onion pakodas for appetizer. For main courses we ordered paneer stuffed capsicum, cashew tikka masala, and madras curry. All dishes were amazing.  The cocktails were amazing. Tried their habanero mango lassie - yummy.

The Vajra restaurant is delightful! In a charming neighborhood, the Vajra has very attentive service, authentic Nepali and Indian food, Eastern decor and a beautiful Kumari tapestry. They have a creative and well crafted cocktail menu. We shared a number of amazing dishes including Momo's, naan, baingan bharta eggplant, cashew shahi korma and chicken chili. All the dishes were generous portions and quite tasty.  The restaurant was at full capacity, had a lot of joyful patrons, and each table seemed to get great personal service. The maitre d' Bipul was lovely. Give it a try, you won't be disappointed!

Amazing food and great service! It was our first time there and the waiter answered all our questions and gave us recommendations. The portions were more generous than we expected and we ended up taking some delicious leftovers home. They have traditional dishes as well as the chef’s own creations. Our favorite was a classic cashew curry with vegetables.
Great service and delicious food. Very good 'special' drinks.

The food was amazing but the drinks were even better, some of the best mixology I have seen in a while. I loved the mix of traditional and non traditional food combinations and differently worth trying for both modern Indian food lovers and ones that want a few changes.
The indian themed cocktails are amazing but pricey as well. The place is one of the best Indian food restaurants in the chicago city area. The butter chicken is a must try.
The food and drinks are wonderful! Do not miss this dining experience!!
We had the most delicious lobster curry. I love this place I cant wait to come back.
Very good indian food. Only wait time is more but worth to wait. Food qty wise it's too less as per price

A delightful experience. Fresh ingredients perfectly cooked, the sauces unctuous, the aromas enveloping, the tastes rich and well-balanced. A vegetarian offering as varied as the non-vegetarian, where the familiar meets the new, where tradition enhances the contemporary and vice versa. Detail over detail show the love with which hospitality is treated here; whether it's the fresh flowers everywhere or the well-stocked aromatics, bitters and dried fruit that enhance the cocktail list. The wine list is keen to showcase smaller producers from familiar places, and here too, somebody put a lot of heart and a lot of thought into its assembly. Last but not least: smiling faces, attentive and unobtrusive service make the experience unique.
Everything we ate and drank here was spectacular! We’ll certainly be coming back to try out other things on the menu.
AMAZING - the food was fabulous although I do wish they had warned us about the bone in chicken - ended up having to chew a little carefully
Authentic and fresh! Excellent service!
Fabulous Indian cuisine. Not like the garbage in the burbs. Reasonable prices, excellent table service. Small seating. Order it all. Take some home for later!

One of my favorite Indian restaurant. The food has an authentic Indian taste and not spicy but flavors are great. The ambience is good. The cocktails list is small but good drinks. The food  here have authentic flavors to it.

The dining experience here was outstanding! The goat steak was phenomenal, as was the saffron rice and the pistachio ice cream. The service was extremely friendly and we were seated right away, despite being about 15 minutes early to our reservation. Oh and get the gruyere naan for sure!

So maybe this place was hyped up a bit too much and that's probably why I didn't think it was as amazing as everyone else did. The food was just good. That's it. It's maybe my fifth favorite Indian restaurant within the city and it won't even stand up next to the ones in the suburbs. That being said some of the dishes were pretty well done, like the Chaat, the goat Momo's, the Paneer Tandoori, the Gruyere Cheese Naan, and the Shahi Korma. I think the Pistachio Paan Kulfi wasn't even good though. That is not what actual Kulfi tastes like and adding paan to if did not make it better. And my friend said she's had better Kulfi from Costco. The ambiance was nice, the service was excellent, and the drinks were okay. I would probably give this place a 3.5, but I'm rounding up.

Vajra represent new vision to Nepali/Indian food. Located on not so busy area with ample of street parking. Food served we're above my expectation, served with apealing look. Great selection of wines and cocktail. Deseart still hanging on my tongue. I recommend every one give a try, Vajra will make you satisfied.
Delightful experience. The service was attentive, the flavors were distinctive, the ambience was intimate, yet relaxed.
Great food, great service, amazing ambiance
Good food and complimented with great drinks.  Well priced as well. Highly recommend it.
Loved everything!!
Excellent Indian food
Awesome experience,must try cocktails and goat
Great food
Delicious food and really friendly staff. The cocktails were very fun and unique. Will definitely go back.
Wonderful Indian restaurant, really enjoyed the fresh naan and biryani!

Great neighborhood spot You must try! This spot is absolutely amazing. I live right down the street and finally got the chance to check it out. Every dish was bursting with flavors, service was great and the ambiance pulled it all together. We will definitely be coming back for more soon.

From the minute we sat down I knew this place was gonna be great. First off, the service was great and I have zero complaints. Taylor was our server and did a wonderful job. Most importantly, the food was spectacular. We got a couple appetizers, the Lamb Tikka Masala and the Lobster Curry, a side dish of spinach and paneer, and the Naan. Hands down the BEST Nepalese food I’ve ever had, and I’ve had it all over the U.S. I would even argue that this is the best restaurant in Chicago. Amazing cocktail list, extensive wine list, several herbal teas to choose from, and a menu that’ll keep you coming back again and again. Give this place a shot, they deserve it, and you deserve it too.
Great Indian food!
Big fan of curry and this place did not disappoint!  Highly recommend for anyone looking for an Indian/Nepalese restaurant.  Great food, drinks, and staff.
Came here with my boyfriend for our anniversary dinner and it was AMAZING 🤤 food, service, ambiance, everything!!! If you love Indian food, this is the spot.
